Method Overloading: It happens when two methods have same name but different parameters in the same class.

Imagine you have a calculator, sometimes you add 2 numbers, sometime you add 3 numbers.
So, even though the action is the same, the number of inputs are different.
Example Code:
class Calculator{
  void add(int a, int b){
  System.out.println(a+b);
  }
 void add(int a, int b, int c){
  System.out.println(a+b+c);
  }
}

public class Main{
    Calculator c= new Calculator();
    c.add(2,10);
    c.add(5,4,6);
}
